INSERT INTO `toon_messages` VALUES(360, 363, 1105, 'Hello Jagdish,\r\n\r\nI really LOVE the visual quality of your work. However, the original assignment said: "I need a head and bust caricature of an unnerved MARGARET THATCHER speaking in British parliament, while tearing down a silly American cone-shaped party hat from her head and exclaiming the famous phrase: ''No, no, no! I want my money back!''\r\n\r\nThe words are just to explain the mood, but not to be in the image. If this turns out great, we will order quite a few more like that."\r\n\r\nWhile age, hair, dress etc. are all just perfect, what you have sent us is a way too static and calm looking character. She is not mad and aggressive enough while TEARING her hat from her head, shouting "No, no, no! I want my money back!"\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, she could do with somewhat more exaggerated facial features, too, be bending forward over her pulpit towards her imaginary audience, and her cap should be AMERICAN (stars and stripes) not British like right now.\r\n\r\nPlease let''s do this better and a little more comical, Jagdish, and you''ll have two more orders coming right away. And please put her on a plain white background for easier cutout later. Thanks.\r\n', '', 1, '2012-03-30 06:33:56');
INSERT INTO `toon_messages` VALUES(361, 265, 1105, 'Hi Marcel, have a look once again n let me know any correction.....always welcome...\r\nThank you', '', 1, '2012-03-31 03:56:14');
INSERT INTO `toon_messages` VALUES(362, 363, 1105, 'Okay Jagdish, now she is much more but really too aggressive, almost like a mad dog. I am afraid no one would want to put this on their T-shirt. There still ought to be a clear comic element about the whole situation. And she''s still not TEARING her hat from her head. Presently, if I had to choose, I''d like the first one better. But that''s too bland, as I explained before. Sorry not to be more enthusiastic.', '', 1, '2012-03-31 07:16:39');
