INSERT INTO `toon_orders` VALUES(1434, 163, 0, 533, 318, 198, 2, 1, 119.90, 60.00, 'Description of Scene:\r\n\r\nThe scene will be from Super Mario Brothers.\r\n\r\nMy wife will be princess peach.  Please refer to the wedding photo that shows her red dress and use this color and style for her dress.  Also, since she’ll be a princess, please add a silver tiara and white gloves that go halfway up her forearms. \r\n\r\nMy character will be Mario.  Please put him in his red and white outfit (like in the photo).   Also, my name is Gabe, so please put a “G” on Mario’s hat instead of an “M”.  \r\n\r\nAs for the scene, the princess will be prisoner in Bowser’s castle.  I’ve included an example of Bowser’s castle, you can use this castle and scale it down so that it does not take up most of the photo.  If this castle is too big, you can create/use a smaller castle.  One note on the castle, you can deviate from the photo I’ve shown you in terms of castle design and background if necessary, but if you can use this castle as a template, I do like the overall color scheme and think the lava and surrounding the castle and the dark sky with lightning is a nice touch.\r\n\r\nThe princess will be atop the castle (standing outside on  one of the rooftops, reaching down towards Mario).  Mario will be climbing up the castle to rescue the princess.  One of Mario’s hands will be holding onto the wall and Mario will be looking up towards the princess.  The other hand will be aimed down towards Bowser, and Mario will be throwing a fire ball at Bowser.  Please try to capture the essence of Mario throwing the fire ball using the picture provided.  I like the motion ring of fire near his hand and the design of the fireball in the picture.  Bowser will be on the ground level of the looking up at Mario with an angry snarl (big, sharp teeth) on his face with both claws raised up towards Mario.   I didn’t have enough space to upload a photo of Bowser, but a lot images can easily be found  by doing a basic Google search.  Use your artistic judgment and find one that fit’s the style of the picture.\r\n\r\nOn the ground level of the castle, please add Yoshi, since he will be our transportation.  Again, I didn’t have room to upload a photo of yoshi, but he’s a green dinosaur.  A quick Google search will bring up plenty of images to work off.  Also, if it’s not too much, please add Dry Bones walking towards Yoshi.  He’s a skeleton version of a Dinosaur from the Mario brothers franchise and can be found pretty easily with any Google search.  My wife and I both like him, and he adds comedic value to the background.\r\n\r\nSince there was limited space for uploading photos, you can either use photos you find online as a template for Bowser, Yoshi, and Dry Bones, or I can email you the photos directly if you want.  Just email me and I can get them to you fairly quickly.', 0, 'other', 'artist paid', 'Paid', '2012-12-10 13:01:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'Dec 21, 2012', '2012-12-21 13:02:17', '2012-12-19', 1, 'My experience with Rodel was great.  He was very accommodating of my requests and asked great questions to make sure he understood the concept I was looking for.  Artistically, his work was very good.  The caricatures are representative of us, and th', '2012-12-19 00:45:56', '2012-12-21 11:02:17');
